WEBVTT

1
00:01:37.970 --> 00:01:39.750
Yes, right.

2
00:01:41.060 --> 00:01:42.950
Yes, of course.

3
00:01:42.950 --> 00:01:44.850
We'll send it over tonight!

4
00:01:46.550 --> 00:01:50.880
Yes, we're truly sorry. 
We hope you'll continue—

5
00:01:55.610 --> 00:02:00.260
Couldn't he have done a smooth handover 
of tasks before leaving on his trip?

6
00:02:02.750 --> 00:02:04.500
It came out of nowhere.

7
00:02:04.500 --> 00:02:06.640
And he's overseas, to boot.

8
00:02:06.640 --> 00:02:10.870
Sasaki-san, I'm sorry! 
I forgot one of the estimates!

9
00:02:10.870 --> 00:02:13.850
Call the client and let them know first.

10
00:02:13.850 --> 00:02:15.380
Sorry, Sasaki-san!

11
00:02:15.630 --> 00:02:19.280
The Itou-kun who joined us 
this year is AWOL. What do I do?

12
00:02:19.280 --> 00:02:21.920
What? Wasn't he in charge 
of some documents?

13
00:02:21.920 --> 00:02:25.140
That's exactly it. He even 
took them home with him.

14
00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:30.270
Got it. I'll go call on him.

15
00:02:30.270 --> 00:02:31.730
Text me his address.

16
00:02:31.730 --> 00:02:32.880
Will do!

17
00:02:57.550 --> 00:02:58.800
Oh, crap!

18
00:03:02.010 --> 00:03:03.040
See you tomorrow.

19
00:03:05.030 --> 00:03:06.810
Thank you for your patience.

20
00:03:07.210 --> 00:03:12.110
The last train for Shimaida is departing 
from platform number 2.

21
00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:23.380
Gah.

22
00:03:48.400 --> 00:03:49.360
Huh?

23
00:03:56.370 --> 00:03:58.100
Damn it, I'm out.

24
00:04:01.890 --> 00:04:03.940
Today, I need to make an order form,

25
00:04:03.940 --> 00:04:07.300
go say hi to a new supplier, and then...

26
00:04:07.300 --> 00:04:09.620
Excuse me, Sasaki-san.

27
00:04:09.890 --> 00:04:13.190
One of my family members 
just collapsed and got hospitalized...

28
00:04:13.190 --> 00:04:15.990
Oh, it's okay. Go see them.

29
00:04:15.990 --> 00:04:18.450
If you've got any urgent work, 
I'll take care of it.

30
00:04:18.450 --> 00:04:20.820
Thank you so much!

31
00:04:20.820 --> 00:04:23.500
Hello? Yeah, I'll be right there.

32
00:04:23.500 --> 00:04:24.760
Got it.

33
00:04:28.910 --> 00:04:31.660
It's all this. 
I'm sorry to leave it to you.

34
00:04:31.660 --> 00:04:36.270
Sorry, Sasaki-san, that Itou-kun 
isn't here today either.

35
00:04:36.270 --> 00:04:37.410
What do I do?

36
00:04:38.750 --> 00:04:40.150
Sasaki-san?!

37
00:05:00.540 --> 00:05:05.900
Sasaki! I can't take this anymore!

38
00:05:05.900 --> 00:05:09.830
You're doing great, man. 
Keep doing what you're doing.

39
00:05:09.830 --> 00:05:10.600
Okay.

40
00:05:40.790 --> 00:05:42.940
I'm back, everyone!

41
00:05:42.940 --> 00:05:46.090
I brought souvenirs. 
Make sure our clients get them.

42
00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:49.630
What's wrong?

43
00:05:49.630 --> 00:05:52.050
Don't tell me you're slacking 
because of the rain!

44
00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:03.820
It's finally over... 
The 14 straight workdays of death.

45
00:06:04.730 --> 00:06:07.020
I somehow got through it.

46
00:06:07.660 --> 00:06:10.490
What did we do to deserve this?

47
00:06:16.550 --> 00:06:19.380
And this blasted rain just won't let up.

48
00:06:25.420 --> 00:06:26.890
Oh, there you are.

49
00:06:27.390 --> 00:06:28.890
What's up?

50
00:06:29.250 --> 00:06:32.140
Long time no see, Tayama-san.

51
00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:36.140
Are you all out of energy? 
I kinda need you for something.

52
00:06:39.140 --> 00:06:40.680
Sure, if I can be of help.

53
00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:46.530
Hey, teru teru bozu charms 
for good weather.

54
00:06:47.070 --> 00:06:48.990
This takes me back.

55
00:06:49.630 --> 00:06:53.060
The manager hangs them up 
every year during rainy season.

56
00:06:53.060 --> 00:06:57.980
We let kids who visit draw faces on them, 
and we employees draw some, too.

57
00:06:57.980 --> 00:06:59.040
Huh...

58
00:06:59.370 --> 00:07:02.540
I was told to do my share, but...

59
00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:08.100
I get it. I suck at this, don't I?

60
00:07:08.100 --> 00:07:09.050
No...

61
00:07:09.300 --> 00:07:11.820
Take a long, hard look and say that again.

62
00:07:11.820 --> 00:07:15.310
Art is individuality. Art is expression.

63
00:07:17.870 --> 00:07:19.560
There you have it.

64
00:07:20.080 --> 00:07:21.850
Draw some for me, Sasaki-san.

65
00:07:24.830 --> 00:07:26.620
Draw, huh?

66
00:07:26.620 --> 00:07:28.390
Not your strong suit?

67
00:07:28.390 --> 00:07:30.200
Well...

68
00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:33.720
I do doodle to keep me awake 
during meetings,

69
00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:36.450
but I don't know if that can 
truly be called drawing.

70
00:07:39.910 --> 00:07:40.910
Done.

71
00:07:45.710 --> 00:07:49.720
Why the manager? 
It really looks like her, too.

72
00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:53.220
Man, that's so funny.

73
00:07:55.190 --> 00:07:57.460
I did draw your manager,

74
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:02.280
so you're next.

75
00:08:04.610 --> 00:08:06.020
Hey, that's cute.

76
00:08:06.020 --> 00:08:08.110
You were really easy to draw.

77
00:08:11.490 --> 00:08:13.520
Must be because you're 
always looking at me.

78
00:08:16.870 --> 00:08:18.750
Guess I'll draw you, too.

79
00:08:31.470 --> 00:08:32.760
Wow, that's good.

80
00:08:33.130 --> 00:08:34.500
What, this?

81
00:08:35.110 --> 00:08:36.140
The cigarette.

82
00:08:38.490 --> 00:08:42.170
I'm pretty fond of rainy days.

83
00:08:42.170 --> 00:08:44.460
The smoke is more visible,

84
00:08:44.990 --> 00:08:48.120
and it even tastes better than usual.

85
00:08:49.110 --> 00:08:51.130
But I've been so busy,

86
00:08:51.130 --> 00:08:54.140
I completely forgot about all that.

87
00:08:55.920 --> 00:08:58.480
It's because I smoke here that I...

88
00:08:59.350 --> 00:09:00.920
I...

89
00:09:05.870 --> 00:09:06.540
Yeah.

90
00:09:07.570 --> 00:09:10.140
Good night, Sasaki-san.

91
00:09:36.860 --> 00:09:38.570
Damn it.

92
00:09:38.570 --> 00:09:40.360
I forgot to turn off the alarm.

93
00:09:40.360 --> 00:09:43.420
I mean, I was so tired, 
I dozed off next to Tayama-san.

94
00:09:43.420 --> 00:09:45.170
I need to rest all day...

95
00:09:45.170 --> 00:09:45.910
Huh?

96
00:09:47.390 --> 00:09:48.520
The heck?

97
00:09:48.920 --> 00:09:51.050
W-Wait, is this...

98
00:09:51.050 --> 00:09:52.360
Tayama-san?

99
00:09:56.480 --> 00:10:00.250
Tayama-san, this is oil-based ink...

100
00:11:15.110 --> 00:11:15.970
Time to eat—

101
00:11:15.970 --> 00:11:20.140
Didn't you say you were 
laying off the ramen for a while?

102
00:11:20.750 --> 00:11:24.140
It's fine. I'll work off what I eat.

103
00:11:24.140 --> 00:11:25.560
You don't say.

104
00:11:26.130 --> 00:11:29.480
I'm sorry to break it to you 
when you're all motivated to work,

105
00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:31.260
but you're getting off early today.

106
00:11:31.260 --> 00:11:36.280
Huh? Tell me that 
before I take my meal break.

107
00:11:37.160 --> 00:11:38.940
Can you blame me?

108
00:11:38.940 --> 00:11:41.920
We're not getting any footfall today. 
I don't want to waste money on pay.

109
00:11:41.920 --> 00:11:45.160
And you're the most flexible 
when it comes to shifts.

110
00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:51.400
Or would you rather stay and help check 
the expiry dates on the frozen foods?

111
00:11:51.400 --> 00:11:53.050
All right, I'll head out.

112
00:11:57.700 --> 00:12:03.300
Man, if she'd told me sooner, I could've 
gone to a ramen place on the way home.

113
00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:05.410
Can't be bothered with makeup.

114
00:12:05.410 --> 00:12:08.810
I'll just buy some booze, smoke one 
in the back, go home, and sleep.

115
00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:11.250
Too bad, Sasaki-san.

116
00:12:11.250 --> 00:12:14.120
Yamada-san won't be here tonight.

117
00:12:16.580 --> 00:12:17.820
Speak of the devil.

118
00:12:19.030 --> 00:12:21.270
He got off at a normal time today?

119
00:12:21.270 --> 00:12:24.360
I could take this chance 
to scare him from behind.

120
00:12:24.360 --> 00:12:25.280
What's up?

121
00:12:25.280 --> 00:12:26.700
Whoa!

122
00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:30.470
But that's old hat by now.

123
00:12:33.600 --> 00:12:34.710
Sasaki-san.

124
00:12:36.200 --> 00:12:37.410
Good evening.

125
00:12:38.230 --> 00:12:39.970
Sasaki-san! Your basket!

126
00:12:42.060 --> 00:12:44.100
Sorry about that! Good evening!

127
00:12:44.590 --> 00:12:46.310
Are you okay?

128
00:12:48.220 --> 00:12:52.720
I-I'm fine. I was just zoning out 
and dropped it.

129
00:12:54.730 --> 00:12:56.060
She's in casual clothes?

130
00:12:56.060 --> 00:12:59.110
Am I allowed to get a pick-me-up 
from Yamada-san out of uniform?

131
00:12:59.790 --> 00:13:02.060
You know you're not. 
Don't you stare at her.

132
00:13:02.060 --> 00:13:04.590
Play it natural. 
Everyone has casual clothes.

133
00:13:04.590 --> 00:13:06.220
Even I wear them!

134
00:13:06.220 --> 00:13:07.370
Sasaki-san.

135
00:13:08.350 --> 00:13:10.380
Here you are.

136
00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:18.900
Thank you very much.

137
00:13:19.340 --> 00:13:23.810
Jugemu Jugemu Goko-no-Surikire 
Kaijari Suigyo No...

138
00:13:26.100 --> 00:13:28.140
Yes, to have with drinks.

139
00:13:28.530 --> 00:13:31.000
Maybe I'll get something, too.

140
00:13:31.800 --> 00:13:34.650
Hey, these cookies are really good.

141
00:13:35.190 --> 00:13:36.720
Is that so?

142
00:13:37.020 --> 00:13:39.530
Oh, they've got a new flavor.

143
00:13:40.180 --> 00:13:44.410
But if I get something sweet, 
I'll also want something savory.

144
00:13:44.960 --> 00:13:46.910
Hmm...

145
00:13:46.910 --> 00:13:47.910
Yamada-san.

146
00:13:50.110 --> 00:13:52.910
You see the three cigarettes here?

147
00:13:53.510 --> 00:13:56.670
Can you assign each 
to one of those snacks?

148
00:13:58.220 --> 00:13:59.280
Okay...

149
00:14:00.920 --> 00:14:01.920
I'm done.

150
00:14:02.240 --> 00:14:03.760
Thank you.

151
00:14:06.310 --> 00:14:07.180
That's the one.

152
00:14:07.790 --> 00:14:11.060
The one that popped out 
is the snack you want.

153
00:14:13.400 --> 00:14:17.330
Oh, sorry. I shouldn't 
be deciding for you.

154
00:14:17.330 --> 00:14:18.560
I'll take it!

155
00:14:22.650 --> 00:14:25.550
Do you use that method often?

156
00:14:26.750 --> 00:14:28.070
I do.

157
00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:31.480
It's more of a superstition for me.

158
00:14:32.220 --> 00:14:35.130
If the first one pops out, 
I'll get to go home early today.

159
00:14:35.130 --> 00:14:37.830
If it's the second one, 
I'll get a day off this week.

160
00:14:38.510 --> 00:14:41.660
And if it's the third one, 
at the register today...

161
00:14:45.040 --> 00:14:46.410
Never mind.

162
00:14:46.860 --> 00:14:48.730
I'm glad you could decide on a snack.

163
00:14:49.420 --> 00:14:51.050
I'll be going now.

164
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:53.240
Take care on your way home.

165
00:14:53.710 --> 00:14:55.770
I will. You too, Sasaki-san.

166
00:15:07.420 --> 00:15:09.280
"And if it's the third one,

167
00:15:09.280 --> 00:15:11.880
Yamada-san will be 
manning a register today."

168
00:15:12.300 --> 00:15:14.860
It's obvious even if you cut yourself off,

169
00:15:14.860 --> 00:15:16.750
Mr. Trying-to-Keep-it-Classy.

170
00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:26.360
If the third one pops out, he'll realize.

171
00:15:26.360 --> 00:15:28.760
If it's the second one, he won't.

172
00:15:29.410 --> 00:15:31.480
And if it's the first...

173
00:15:42.990 --> 00:15:47.950
I think that means something bad's 
going to happen to Sasaki-san.

174
00:15:54.540 --> 00:15:56.260
I've done it now!

175
00:15:56.260 --> 00:15:58.540
I was so distracted by 
Yamada-san in casual wear

176
00:15:58.540 --> 00:16:00.440
that I forgot I had this 
magazine under my arm!

177
00:16:00.440 --> 00:16:03.790
I took it out without paying for it!

178
00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:06.550
Sir.

179
00:16:06.900 --> 00:16:09.210
We take a very dim view of shoplifting.

180
00:16:09.210 --> 00:16:11.690
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

181
00:16:11.690 --> 00:16:14.680
Everybody says that, Sasaki-kun.

182
00:16:17.230 --> 00:16:21.450
I'm truly sorry!
